article.headline: SE Louisiana 68, Texas State 60
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Ricky Woods scored 21 points, including 15 in the second half, to help lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 68-60 victory over Texas State on Thursday night. Southeastern Louisiana (10-10, 4-5 Southland) used a 17-4 run early in the second half to get back in the game after trailing by 16 at halftime. The Lions took at 42-40 lead on a 3-pointer by Quennell Green with 9:47 to play. Wilson also had 12 rebounds, five steals and two blocked shots. Justin Edwards came off the bench to score 17 points for Southeastern Louisiana. Green had 13 and Jonathon Walker added 11. Antwoine Blanchard led Texas State (2-16, 0-7) with 18 points. Brandon Bush added 12 and Charles Dotson 11. Texas State shot 65 percent from the field in the first half but cooled off in the second, shooting just 30 percent. Southeastern Louisiana shot 36 percent in the first half and 55 percent in the second half.
